stylometry: It is more difficult to solve these problems because excel first has to figure out whether to even produce a product or not.  After it figures this out, it then has to figure out how much or how little.  Also, there could be more than one optimal solution.  The algorithm tests all of the possible outcomes based on constraints and it can find different answers.  Once a solution is found it will stop, but there may be more solutions if you test again.  With 0-1 models, Excel can find various combinations that achieve the same outcome.
